body:
rust doc comments have a lot links to the API docs, for example:

```
/// Readers are intended to be composable with one another. Many implementors
/// throughout [`std::io`] take and provide types which implement the `Read`
/// trait.
///
/// Please note that each call to [`read()`] may involve a system call, and
/// therefore, using something that implements [`BufRead`], such as
/// [`BufReader`], will be more efficient.
///
/// [`read()`]: trait.Read.html#tymethod.read
/// [`std::io`]: ../../std/io/index.html
/// [`BufRead`]: trait.BufRead.html
/// [`BufReader`]: struct.BufReader.html
```

the definations of those links seem unnecessary,
api doc link can be automatic generated same as [dart lang doc comment].

[dart lang doc comment]: https://www.dartlang.org/guides/language/language-tour#documentation-comments

is there any plan to link to API docs just like `use` declaration: 

```
/// Readers are intended to be composable with one another. Many implementors
/// throughout [`std::io`] take and provide types which implement the `Read`
/// trait.
///
/// Please note that each call to [`std::io::Read.read()`] may involve a system call, and
/// therefore, using something that implements [`std::io::BufRead`], such as
/// [`std::io::BufReader`], will be more efficient.
```
